───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NAIM Diet Planner — Design Philosophy
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This software embodies the following principles:

1. LOCAL-FIRST — All user data (profile, meal plans, ratings, iteration
   history) is stored exclusively via AsyncStorage on the user's own device.
   No servers. No cloud. No databases outside the phone.

2. ABSOLUTE PRIVACY — No analytics, no crash reporting, no ads, no telemetry.
   The app does not request network permissions for user data. What happens
   on your phone stays on your phone.

3. SELF-EVOLVING (NAIM Philosophy) — The diet plan is not static. Through
   the NAIM iterative loop, users rate meals and the engine regenerates a
   better plan each week. The app learns from feedback, replaces disliked
   meals, and improves with every iteration — entirely locally.

4. FREE SOFTWARE — This is free software in the GNU sense. You are free to
   run, study, share, and modify it. See the GPL v3 license above.

